programme.title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
programme.desc: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

programme.title: Fulham vs Arsenal - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
programme.desc: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

programme.desc: Fulham have only won one of their last 14 Premier League games against Arsenal, a 2-1 victory in December 2023. Indeed, the Cottagers have conceded at least once in each of their last 20 against the Gunners in the competition. After winning five successive league visits to Fulham from 2012-13 to 2022-23, Arsenal have since failed to win at Craven Cottage in both of the last two campaigns. The Gunners last failed to win more consecutive league visits to Fulham in April 1962.

programme.title: Manchester City vs Everton - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8 - Mini match
programme.desc: Manchester City are unbeaten in their last 16 Premier League meetings with Everton since a 0-4 defeat at Goodison Park in January 2017. Everton are winless in their last 14 away Premier League games against Manchester City since a 2-1 victory in December 2010 during David Moyes’ first spell in charge. Only at Man Utd, Liverpool, Arsenal, and Chelsea have they ever had longer winless away runs in the competition.

programme.title: Tottenham Hotspur vs Aston Villa - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
programme.desc: None of the last 20 Premier League matches between Tottenham Hotspur and Aston Villa have been drawn since a 1-1 stalemate in May 2012. Only two fixtures in the competition’s history have ever had more successive games without a draw: Newcastle v Spurs and Chelsea v Crystal Palace. Aston Villa have won four of their last six Premier League games against Tottenham Hotspur, as many as their previous 29 beforehand.

programme.title: Liverpool vs Manchester United - English Premier League 2025/2026 Week 8
programme.desc: Liverpool have lost just one of their last 14 Premier League meetings with Manchester United, a 1-2 defeat at Old Trafford in August 2022. Each episode features a different legend, who is invited to design a line-up following different indications; the best opponents they faced, the best players from LALIGA EA SPORTS 23/24 and the best teammates they played with.Nine LaLiga legends are invited to choose their ideal eleven. Each episode features a different legend selecting from the best opponents they faced, their favourite teammates they played with and the cream of current LaLiga talent.

programme.title: Boca Juniors vs River Plate - QF 2000
programme.desc: 2000: One of the most remembered Superclasicos. Boca's Los Xeneizes produced a sublime second-half display to win 3-0 and take the tie 4-2 on aggregate.

programme.title: Boca Juniors vs Santos - Final 2003
programme.desc: 2003: Boca won 5-1 on aggregate with rising star Carlos Tevez notching one of the goals in a 3-1 triumph in the away leg.

programme.title: Sao Paulo vs Atletico PR - Final 2005
programme.desc: 2005: With goals from Amoroso, Fabao, Luizao and Diego Tardelli, Sao Paulo became the first Brazilian team with three titles in the continental tournament.

programme.title: Cruzeiro vs Estudiantes - Final 2009
programme.desc: 2009: Kléber scored two goals in less than five minutes, bringing Cruzeiro to victory and two champion of the Libertadores.

programme.title: Corinthians vs Vasco - QF 2012
programme.desc: 2012: Paulinho’s dramatic 88th minute header won the tie and put Corinthians into the semi-final of the Copa Libertadores at the expense of Brazilian rivals Vasco.

programme.title: Once Caldes vs Boca Juniors - Final 2004
programme.desc: 2004: The Colombian team Once Caldes made history and won the unprecedented title by beating Boca Juniors 2-0 on penalties.
